{
    "id": "quaternionutil",
    "lang": "en-us",
    "name": "QuaternionUtil",
    "description": "Create and blend rotations the safe way: build a facing from angles or a direction, smoothly turn toward a target, and convert rotations to readable angles.",
    "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/quaternionutil",
    "tags": [
        "uniscript",
        "quaternionutil",
        "rotation",
        "quaternion",
        "lookrotation",
        "euler"
    ],
    "previous": {
        "name": "VectorUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/vectorutil"
    },
    "next": {
        "name": "ListUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/listutil"
    },
    "content": [
        {
            "id": "block-001",
            "tag": "h1",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "QuaternionUtil"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-002",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "A **quaternion** is how the game stores a **rotation** — which way an object is facing. The math behind quaternions is complex, but the good news is you almost never touch it directly. `QuaternionUtil` gives you simple ways to build a rotation from everyday angles or a direction, smoothly turn toward a target, and read a rotation back as plain angles."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-003",
            "tag": "important",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "You think in **angles** (degrees), the game thinks in **quaternions**. This page is the bridge: `New` and `Euler` turn angles into a rotation, and `ToVector` turns a rotation back into angles."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-004",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Building a rotation from angles"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-005",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "The easiest way to make a rotation is from three angles in degrees: how much to tilt on each axis. The `y` angle is the common left/right turn."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-006",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Face 90 degrees to the right (turn around the up axis).",
                "quaternion facing = QuaternionUtil.New(0.0, 90.0, 0.0);",
                "UniObjectUtil.SetRotation(this, facing);",
                "",
                "// Same thing, but starting from a vector3 of angles.",
                "vector3 angles = VectorUtil.New(0.0, 90.0, 0.0);",
                "quaternion facing2 = QuaternionUtil.Euler(angles);"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-007",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`New(x, y, z)`", "A rotation from three angles in degrees."],
                ["`Euler(vector)`", "A rotation from a `vector3` of angles in degrees."],
                ["`Identity()`", "The \"no rotation\" value — facing straight ahead, untilted."],
                ["`ToVector(rotation)`", "Turns a rotation back into a readable `vector3` of angles."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-008",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Facing toward a direction"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-009",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`LookRotation` builds the rotation needed to point along a direction — exactly what you want to aim at a target. It takes the direction to look along **and** an \"up\" direction (almost always `VectorUtil.Up()`)."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-010",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Turn to face a target.",
                "vector3 myPos     = UniObjectUtil.GetWorldPosition(this);",
                "vector3 targetPos = UniObjectUtil.GetWorldPosition(target);",
                "vector3 direction = VectorUtil.Normalized(targetPos - myPos);",
                "",
                "quaternion look = QuaternionUtil.LookRotation(direction, VectorUtil.Up());",
                "UniObjectUtil.SetRotation(this, look);"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-011",
            "tag": "warning",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`LookRotation` needs **two** arguments — the direction and an up vector. Calling it with only the direction will not work. When in doubt, pass `VectorUtil.Up()` as the second argument."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-012",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Turning smoothly over time"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-013",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Snapping instantly to a new rotation can look harsh. `Slerp` blends from one rotation to another so an object **turns** toward its target instead of jumping."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-014",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`Slerp(from, to, t)`", "A rotation partway between two quaternions (`t` is `0`–`1`)."],
                ["`SlerpV3(from, to, t)`", "The same, but you give the two rotations as `vector3` angle values."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-015",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Smoothly rotate toward 'look' a little each frame.",
                "quaternion current = UniObjectUtil.GetRotation(this);",
                "quaternion turned  = QuaternionUtil.Slerp(current, look, Time.DeltaTime() * 5.0);",
                "UniObjectUtil.SetRotation(this, turned);"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-016",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Full method reference"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-017",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Returns",
                "Method",
                "Parameters"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`quaternion`", "`Identity`", "—"],
                ["`quaternion`", "`New`", "`float x, float y, float z`"],
                ["`quaternion`", "`Slerp`", "`quaternion from, quaternion to, float speed`"],
                ["`quaternion`", "`SlerpV3`", "`vector3 from, vector3 to, float speed`"],
                ["`quaternion`", "`LookRotation`", "`vector3 direction, vector3 up`"],
                ["`quaternion`", "`Euler`", "`vector3 vector`"],
                ["`vector3`", "`ToVector`", "`quaternion rotation`"]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-018",
            "tag": "tip",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Need positions and directions instead of rotations? See [VectorUtil](/docs/uniscript/en-us/vectorutil). To apply a rotation to an object, see [UniObjectUtil's SetRotation](/docs/uniscript/en-us/uniobjectutil#block-013)."
        }
    ]
}
